    "body": "### Description\n\n`src/ctime_tests.c` currently exercises `secp256k1_schnorrsig_sign32` under Valgrind/CHECKMEM, but does not call the public `secp256k1_schnorrsig_sign_custom` entry point.\n\n`sign_custom` is not only an alias: it accepts optional `extraparams` (including a custom nonce function) and variable message length before calling the shared internal signer. Functional tests cover it, but not under the constant-time CHECKMEM harness.\n\nThis PR adds a minimal direct call to `secp256k1_schnorrsig_sign_custom(..., NULL)` with secret material undefined under CHECKMEM (default nonce path).\n\n### Coverage gap (why)\n\nPlanted local-only synthetic mutations unique to the `sign_custom` entry (secret-dependent branch / secret-dependent static table load that do not change signature output) were **not** detected by the existing ctime suite, but **were** detected after this one-call addition. A constant-work control mutation remained clean.\n\nThis is a **test-coverage** improvement. **No production cryptographic code is modified.** This PR does **not** claim a real production vulnerability in unmodified libsecp256k1.\n\n### Change\n\n- `src/ctime_tests.c` only (+11 lines)\n- No mutation code\n- No new dependencies\n\n### Build / test\n\n```bash\ncmake -B build \\\n  -DSECP256K1_VALGRIND=ON \\\n  -DSECP256K1_BUILD_CTIME_TESTS=ON \\\n  -DSECP256K1_ENABLE_MODULE_SCHNORRSIG=ON \\\n  -DSECP256K1_ENABLE_MODULE_EXTRAKEYS=ON \\\n  -DSECP256K1_ENABLE_MODULE_ECDH=ON \\\n  -DSECP256K1_ENABLE_MODULE_RECOVERY=ON \\\n  -DSECP256K1_ENABLE_MODULE_ELLSWIFT=ON \\\n  -DSECP256K1_ENABLE_MODULE_MUSIG=ON\ncmake --build build --target ctime_tests\nvalgrind --error-exitcode=42 ./build/bin/ctime_tests\n```\n\nClean upstream + this test: pass (repeated).  \nSynthetic mutations were local-only and are not included in this branch.\n\n### Limitations\n\n- Default nonce path only; a dedicated custom-nonce callback CHECKMEM case can be a follow-up.",
